## ✅ Part 1 — Pre-Flight Checks Before Every Testing Session

### 1a. Start the Backend Server
Open a terminal in `d:\ASTURA\svakarma-mobile\backend` and run:
```bash
npm run dev
```
**Expected output:**
```
🚀 Svakarma Backend running at http://localhost:5000
📊 Health Check: http://localhost:5000/health
```

### 1b. Confirm Backend is Live
Open your browser and visit: `http://localhost:5000/health`

Expected JSON:
```json
{ "status": "ok", "service": "svakarma-mobile-backend" }
```

### 1c. Start the Mobile App
Open a second terminal in `d:\ASTURA\svakarma-mobile\myapp` and run:
```bash
npx expo start
```

### 1d. ⚠️ Confirm Your LAN IP is Correct
Your phone must be on the **same Wi-Fi network** as your PC. The LAN IP in [`api.js`](file:///d:/ASTURA/svakarma-mobile/myapp/services/api.js) must match your PC's current IP.

**To check your PC's LAN IP:**
```powershell
ipconfig
```
Look for: `IPv4 Address . . . . . . : 192.168.x.x`

Then open [`api.js`](file:///d:/ASTURA/svakarma-mobile/myapp/services/api.js) and confirm line 8:
```js
const DEV_LAN_IP = '10.207.133.221'; // ← Update if your IP changed
```

