## 🔌 Part 3 — Where to Integrate Real APIs (When Your Manager Provides Them)

### 3a. OTP / SMS Gateway APIs
> **File to edit:** [`backend/src/modules/auth/auth.routes.ts`](file:///d:/ASTURA/svakarma-mobile/backend/src/modules/auth/auth.routes.ts) — line ~15

```typescript
// REPLACE THIS MOCK:
const otp = '123456';
otpStorage.set(phone, otp);
console.log(`[OTP Engine] OTP sent to ${phone}: ${otp}`);

// WITH REAL API (e.g. MSG91, Twilio, AWS SNS):
const otp = Math.floor(100000 + Math.random() * 900000).toString();
await smsGateway.sendOTP(phone, otp); // ← call your SMS provider here
otpStorage.set(phone, otp);
```

---

### 3b. Aadhaar eKYC / PAN Verification APIs
> **File to edit:** [`backend/src/modules/auth/auth.routes.ts`](file:///d:/ASTURA/svakarma-mobile/backend/src/modules/auth/auth.routes.ts) — inside `/verify-otp` route

